Team Agreement
Introduction

This document outlines the team agreement for the development of the Hackathon Team Management System. It aims to ensure effective collaboration, well-defined responsibilities, and clear communication among all team members throughout the project duration.

Team Roles and Responsibilities

Project Manager:
Responsible for planning, coordinating tasks, monitoring progress, and overseeing overall project execution.

Documentation Lead:
Manages the creation, updating, and maintenance of all project-related documents and reports.

Lead Developer:
Designs the system architecture and handles the development and implementation of core functionalities.

QA Lead:
Conducts testing activities to ensure the system meets quality standards and project requirements.

Communication Plan

Team communication will be carried out using WhatsApp and face-to-face discussions.

Regular meetings will be conducted to track progress, address issues, and plan upcoming activities.

Decision Making

Project-related decisions will be made through collective discussion and mutual agreement.

In situations where consensus cannot be reached, the Project Manager will make the final decision.

Work Ethics

All team members are expected to complete assigned tasks within the agreed timelines.

Team members will collaborate, support one another, and maintain a respectful working environment.

Any challenges, delays, or risks will be communicated promptly to ensure smooth project execution.

Agreement Acceptance

All team members agree to follow and adhere to this team agreement throughout the development lifecycle of the Hackathon Team Management System.
